Date:  17/5/1951
Source:  Personal Communication
Author:  COLIN GORDON
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote:  If you get behind [on your part of the chain] yell out for the rover, an extra man who [helps out at need] and keeps the chaps `up the chain'. He helps anybody, and will give you a cut up the chain, that is, do jobs for you.
